    "reasoning": "To implement the Rule 90 cellular automaton, I need to follow these steps:\n1. Understand that Rule 90 updates each cell based on the XOR of its left and right neighbors.\n2. Since we have a 512-cell system, I need to handle q[511:0] where q[-1] and q[512] are considered as 0.\n3. The update rule: q_new[i] = q_old[i-1] ^ q_old[i+1] for i in 0..511.\n4. When load is asserted, the system should load the data into q.\n5. Otherwise, on each clock cycle, q should be updated based on the previous state according to Rule 90.\n\nTo ensure correct implementation:\n- Declare all signals as logic.\n- Use a register to store the current state of q.\n- In the sequential block, either load the data when load is asserted, or apply Rule 90 transformation.\n- Apply the XOR operation using the neighboring bits correctly, handling boundary conditions where q[-1] and q[512] are 0.\n- Use always @(*) for combinational logic to derive the next state.\n\nAvoiding syntax errors:\n- Ensure proper bit indexing with correct ranges.\n- Use {q[511], q[510:0]} to properly select bits for XOR operations without using invalid ranges.\n- Keep variable declarations clear and consistent.\n- Follow the module interface exactly.",
    "module": "module TopModule (\n    input clk,\n    input load,\n    input [511:0] data,\n    output logic [511:0] q\n);\n\n    // Register to hold the current state\n    logic [511:0] q_reg;\n\n    // Combinational logic to calculate next state\n    always @(*) begin\n        // Initialize next state\n        logic [511:0] q_next;\n        \n        // For each cell, compute XOR of left and right neighbors\n        // q[-1] is 0, q[512] is 0\n        for (int i = 0; i < 512; i = i + 1) begin\n            logic left, right;\n            \n            // Get left neighbor (q[-1] = 0)\n            if (i == 0)\n                left = 1'b0;\n            else\n                left = q_reg[i-1];\n            \n            // Get right neighbor (q[512] = 0)\n            if (i == 511)\n                right = 1'b0;\n            else\n                right = q_reg[i+1];\n            \n            // Apply Rule 90: center = left XOR right\n            q_next[i] = left ^ right;\n        end\n        \n        // Assign next state\n        q = q_next;\n    end\n\n    // Sequential logic to load or update\n    always @(posedge clk) begin\n        if (load)\n            q_reg <= data;\n        else\n            q_reg <= q;\n    end\n\nendmodule"
